<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-06-10T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-06-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="31" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d31">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363/1140: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-10T15:00:00-05:00">June 10, 1931—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:35 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>78. President Olaya tells me he forwarded by air mail Friday<note n="20" xml:id="d31fn20">June 5.</note> copy of draft of proposed oil bill
                            regulations to Rublee for any comment he may care to make before they
                            are issued.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>